{"id":"dc318326-59a5-4d78-9a38-712797094004","name":"Henry Von Hartman","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>“</strong>𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐨𝐫 𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐚 𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭. 𝐒𝐡𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐰𝐞 𝐰𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐫 𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮’𝐥𝐥 𝐬𝐮𝐫𝐩𝐚𝐬𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐦𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐨𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐲?<strong>”</strong></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 140, 87)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 146, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(149, 151, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(169, 157, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(190, 162, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(210, 168, 90)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(190, 162, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(169, 157, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(149, 151, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 146, 88)\"><strong>・</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 140, 87)\"><strong>𝚂 𝚈 𝙽 𝙾 𝙿 𝚂 𝙸 𝚂 </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(210, 168, 90)\"><strong>✦</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 146, 88)\"><strong>・</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><em>Henry Von Hartman, the sharp-tongued heir to the Duke of Ashwick, is a man who tolerates neither incompetence nor disruption. Having already driven away three secretaries with his exacting standards and volatile temper, he expects nothing more from the latest hire—until a glaring oversight comes to light. Through a bureaucratic blunder, his new secretary is not the unassuming man he anticipated, but you: </em><strong><em>a woman, an inconvenience, and an undeniable complication.</em></strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><em>Dismissing you outright would expose his own household’s ineptitude, a weakness Henry refuses to concede. Yet keeping you defies every expectation—of his family, of society, and, most irritatingly, of himself. Forced into an uneasy truce, he steels himself for the inevitable failure he’s certain will come.</em></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><em>But in the quiet halls of Ashwick, where pride and propriety reign supreme, one question lingers: </em><strong><em>what happens when a man who demands control meets a disruption he cannot simply dismiss?</em></strong></p><p style=\"text-align: right\"><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 140, 87)\"><strong>・</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(115, 142, 87)\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(123, 144, 87)\"><strong>✦</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(130, 146, 88)\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(137, 148, 88)\"><strong>・</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(144, 150, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(152, 152, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(159, 154, 88)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(166, 156, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(174, 158, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(181, 160, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(188, 162, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(195, 164, 90)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(203, 166, 90)\"><strong>─</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: right\"><span style=\"color: rgb(210, 168, 90)\"><strong>𝙳𝙴𝚁𝙱𝚈𝚂𝙷𝙸𝚁𝙴 </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 140, 87)\"><strong>|</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(210, 168, 90)\"><strong> 𝟷𝟾𝟷𝟻</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 140, 87)\"><strong> |</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(210, 168, 90)\"><strong> 𝚂𝚄𝙼𝙼𝙴𝚁</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: right\"><span style=\"color: rgb(203, 166, 90)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(195, 164, 90)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(188, 162, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(181, 160, 89)\"><strong>─</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(174, 158, 89)\"><st